## Phase Roadmap

| Phase | Status | Features |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | ✅ Complete | TCP streaming, WAV file source, client playback, basic buffering |
| 2 | ✅ Complete | Mic capture, multithreading, jitter buffer, packet loss concealment |
| 3 | 🔲 Next | UDP mode, sequence IDs, latency metrics dashboard |
| 4 | 🔲 Future | Opus codec, multi-room sync, WebSocket metrics UI |

---

## Debugging Tips

### Check if server is accepting connections
```bash
ss -tlnp | grep 9001
```

### Monitor packet flow live
```bash
# Count packets per second
tcpdump -i lo port 9001 -q | pv -l -r > /dev/null

# Wireshark on loopback
wireshark -i lo -f "port 9001"
```

### Measure latency with ping as a reference
```bash
ping -i 0.02 192.168.1.42   # 20ms interval = one audio chunk
```

### Enable verbose logging
```bash
./build/audiostream_server --debug 2>&1 | tee server.log
./build/audiostream_client --debug 2>&1 | tee client.log
```

### Watch metrics output

The server and client both print a metrics summary every 10 seconds:

```
┌─ Stream Health ──────────────────────────────
│ Sent:     1500  Recv: 1498  Lost: 2 (0.1%)
│ Latency:  min=12ms  avg=18ms  p95=34ms  max=67ms
│ Buffer:   4/4 chunks (100%)
└──────────────────────────────────────────────
```

