## Resume Bullet Points (copy-paste ready)

> **Real-Time Audio Streaming System** | C++, Linux, TCP/UDP, Multithreading
>
> - Built a low-latency audio streaming system in C++ capable of transmitting real-time audio across networked clients using TCP/UDP sockets
> - Implemented multithreaded audio capture, packet buffering, and playback pipelines to support concurrent real-time streaming workloads
> - Designed a jitter buffer with in-order packet delivery and loss concealment to reduce playback interruptions under unstable network conditions
> - Debugged socket communication, timing issues, and packet loss using Wireshark, tcpdump, and system-level latency metrics instrumentation